    <h2>Privacy Policy</h2>

    <p>ZenBanx Canada Inc. (“ZBC,” “we,” “our,” or “us”), on behalf of DUCA Financial Services Credit Union LTD. (“DUCA”), is committed to protecting and maintaining the confidentiality of information identifiable to you, including your personal, financial and other information (“Personal Information”).</p>
     
    <p>Our privacy practices and this privacy policy (the “Privacy Policy”) are in accordance with the Personal Information Protection and Electronic Documents Act (PIPEDA) and applicable provincial privacy laws and regulations and the Canadian Standards Association (CSA) Model Code for the Protection of Personal Information (CAN/CSA-Q830-96).</p> 
     
    <p>This Privacy Policy applies to any person that has requested or has subscribed for the ZenBanx Canada Account and ZenBanx-branded services offered by DUCA (the “Services”) and is intended to help you better understand the following:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>What information we collect from you,</li>
        <li>Why we collect your information,</li>
        <li>Who we share or disclose member information to,</li>
        <li>How we protect your information,</li>
        <li>Accessing, updating and removing your Personal Information, and</li>
        <li>Providing or withdrawing your consent to our collection, use or disclosure of your Personal Information in accordance with this privacy policy.</li>
    </ul>
     
    <h4>Your Consent</h4>
     
    <p>By using or inquiring about our Services, you agree to be bound by this Privacy Policy and consent to the collection, use, sharing and protection of your Personal Information in accordance with this Privacy Policy.  Should you withdraw your consent to the use of your Personal Information in accordance with this Privacy Policy, you must discontinue your use of our Services and the Account.</p>
     
    <h4>Collection of Personal Information</h4>

    <p class="">We may collect Personal Information in a number of ways when you use our Services, or through your ongoing interactions with us.  We may collect the following information about you:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>Identification information, including your name, Social Insurance Number, e-mail address, mailing address, phone number and birth date (collectively “Personal Information”).  </li>
        <li>Information arising from your use of our Services, including your account balance(s), transaction history, payment history, and email, telephone or other communications with us.</li>
        <li>Additional information for identity matching and credit history purposes.</li>
        <li>Information collected via cookies when you visit our app(s) or website(s) to provide you with better Services and features on our website.  The types of cookies that we may use are "session cookies" and "persistent cookies."  You may adjust your browser or mobile device settings to notify you when a cookie is about to be sent or you may configure your browser to refuse cookies automatically.  However, without cookies you may not have access to certain Services and features on our website(s) that rely on cookies for their functionality.</li>
        <li>Your location if you enable your computer or mobile device to send us location information.  You may be able to change the settings on your computer or mobile device to prevent it from providing us with such information.   However, you may not have access to certain Services and features that rely on location information for their functionality.</li>
        <li>Information from third parties, including government agencies and registries, law enforcement authorities and public records, credit reporting agencies, other financial institutions, service providers, agents and other organizations with whom you make arrangements, employers and personal references you have provided, and persons authorized to act on your behalf under a power of attorney or other legal authority.</li>
        <li>Other information we may collect with your consent, or as permitted or required by law.</li>
    </ul>
     
    <p class="">The collection, use and disclosure of your Personal Information may be obtained in a variety of manners, and may be express or implied.  You agree that we are permitted to collect your Personal Information indirectly, or without your consent and knowledge when the collection is clearly in your interest and consent cannot be obtained in a timely way.</p>
     
    <h4>Why We Collect and Uses of Personal Information</h4>
     
    <p class="">We do not use or disclose Personal Information for purposes other than those for which it was collected, except with the consent of the individual or as required by law.  We collect Personal Information for purposes including, but not limited to, the ones described below:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>To provide our Services to you and administer your Account, including verifying your identity or contacting you regarding your Account.</li>
        <li>To understand customer requirements to improve and develop our Services to you, including analyzing your financial needs or marketing or recommending other products or Services.</li>
        <li>To meet legal and regulatory requirement, including anti-money laundering and “know your customer” legal requirements.</li>
        <li>To detect and prevent fraudulent, inaccurate, unauthorized or illegal activities.</li>
        <li>To manage and assess our risks, operations and relationships with you.</li>
        <li>To evaluate and process your applications, transactions, claims, accounts, and to assess your eligibility for requested products or Services offered by us.</li>
        <li>For any other purpose to which you consent or that is permitted or required by applicable law. </li>
    </ul>
     
    <h4>Disclosure of Personal Information</h4>
     
    <p>We may disclose your Personal Information in a number of circumstances, including:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>To our subsidiaries or affiliates, for reasons including legal and regulatory purposes, managing credit risk and other business risks, performing analytics, ensuring that we have updated information about you and providing other products or Services to you.  </li>
        <li>To third parties or service providers, in order for us to provide our Services to you, including identity verification services, and monitoring and managing fraud and other criminal activity.</li>
        <li>To credit bureaus, credit reporting agencies and to your current or future creditors for the purpose of maintaining your credit history and providing credit references.</li>
        <li>If we are acquired by or merged with a third-party entity, or if we sell any of our business, we may transfer or assign your Personal Information as part of such merger, sale or other change of control.</li>
        <li>For any other purpose to which you consent or that is permitted or required by law.</li>
        <li>If we believe in good faith it is appropriate or necessary to take precautions against liability.</li>
    </ul>
     
    <h4>Security and Retention of Personal Information</h4>
     
    <p>We take seriously our responsibility to protect the security, integrity and privacy of your information from loss, theft, unauthorized access, disclosure, use, copying, change, modification or erasure.  Your Account and Personal Information is protected by a password for your privacy and security. We take commercially reasonable efforts to safeguard your Personal Information through security measures appropriate to the sensitivity of the information.  We restrict access to your Personal Information to only our authorized associates and service providers who require access only in order to fulfill our Services, and even then, those individuals are bound by strict confidentiality obligations. We retain your Personal Information for only as long as required for the reason(s) that it was collected or necessary as required by applicable law.</p>
     
    <h4>Accessing and Updating Your Information</h4>
     
    <p>You may review or verify your Personal Information by viewing your Account statements or logging into your Account online or via the app. You agree to make sure your Personal Information is accurate, complete and up-to-date.  If you have any questions or concerns about this Policy, please contact Customer Care during “Business Hours (8am to 8pm Eastern Standard Time), Monday through Friday (excluding bank holidays) (“Business Day”) at (877) ZEN-BANX (936-2269); Email: HELP@zenbanx.ca; Mailing address: 1 Yonge Street Ste. 1900, Toronto, Ontario M5E 1E5.  If your question or concern has still not been resolved by Customer Care, please contact the Ombudsman at ombudsman@zenbanx.ca.</p>
     
    <h4>Changes to our Privacy Policy</h4>
     
    <p>We may change this Agreement anytime but will notify you of any material changes that affect our treatment of your Personal Information, thirty (30) days prior to any such change.  Your continued use of your Account means that you accept and agree to the changes.</p>

